wikipedia_page.main: David John MacRae Carnegie, 14th Earl of Northesk (3 November 1954 – 28 March 2010), styled Lord Rosehill between 1975 and 1994, was a British hereditary peer, landowner and member of the House of Lords.

response: *David Carnegie, 14th Earl of Northesk (1954–2010), Scottish peer
*David Carnegie, 14th Earl of Northesk, 55, Scottish peer, member of the House of Lords.

Lord Northesk is an agnatic descendant of David Carnegie, 2nd Earl of Northesk. He inherited the earldom on the death of his eighth cousin once removed, David Carnegie, 14th Earl of Northesk, on 28 March 2010.Earl of Northesk, Peerage News, Google Groups, 30 March 2010.
